The paper proposes a framework for updating Deep Learning-based traffic classification models during active operations. This involves the use of a self-learned discriminator and autonomous self-labeling model to generate new datasets during active operations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
